snippet.textDisplay: It reminds me of the time when I traveled to Thar/Mithi for work in 2011 and 2012. I stayed there for a alomost three months. Despite the severe climate, it was a lovely place where I had a pleasant time. The area was incredibly tranquil, and I took the opportunity to visit nearby cities like Umarkot and Nagar Parker. I even explored an ancient Mandir that was around 2500 years old. There's a wealth of history there that I believe deserves more exploration. The beauty of the place is especially striking after rainfall. The video does a great job of capturing the local culture and traditional dress. I would relish the chance to visit again
